Troops of 34 Artillery Brigade, Nigerian Army (NA) have neutralised two gunmen and arrested four other suspected members of the outlawed Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB) and its armed affiliate, Eastern Security Network (ESN) in a fierce gun battle along Orlu – Orsu Road.  
    
According to army spokesperson, Onyema Nwachukwu, the troops, while on routine patrol made contact with elements of IPOB/ESN around the general area of Aluminium Company and All Saints Church.  